      "message": "I started using \"subset\u0027 because domain seemed confusing when I was working on GrTextureEffect. Whether it referred to a true domain or range in the mathematical sense depends on what part of the pipeline you\u0027re thinking about. From the GrTextureEffect\u0027s perspective it seemed like the rectangle was more of a range (the input coords are unbounded and the output is limited to the \"subset\"). From the perspective of the actual call to sample the texture in the shader it is a domain, in that it is the set of legal texture coords. I settled on \"subset\" because its vaguer and doesn\u0027t specifically mean the input or output set of a function.",
